v:4 c:$ m:portfolio role:dev x:vue-css-layered-fx
gate: OPEN

task: Port the multi-layer `.glass-entity` recursive component from sdui-proto into a Vue 3 SFC. Preserve layer contract (bg / ambient::before / glass-body / wash / center-glow / core-dot / content / bevel / bottom-glow) and status-driven animations (calm / alert / notify / warn / alarm / dim / dream).

requires: [vue, tailwind]
source: /Users/denistka/Projects/sdui-proto/src/assets/styles/sdui.css#L1-L267
out:
  - app/src/components/glass/GlassEntity.vue
  - app/src/components/glass/glass-entity.css
  - app/src/components/glass/types.ts
  - app/src/components/glass/__demo__/GlassPlayground.vue

api-contract:
  props:
    - status: 'calm' | 'alert' | 'notify' | 'warn' | 'alarm' | 'dim' | 'dream' (default 'calm')
    - radius?: string (default var(--e-radius))
    - delay?: string (entry stagger)
    - intensity?: number 0-1 (default 0.6)
    - interactive?: boolean
    - hideAmbient?: boolean
    - hideBottom?: boolean
    - hideWash?: boolean
    - pureLayout?: boolean (decoupler mode for SDUI wrappers)
  slots:
    - default → layer-content
    - bg → layer-bg (custom dynamic background, e.g. canvas/gradient)

constraints:
  - DOM order must match sdui-proto: layer-bg → layer-glass(::before bevel, layer-content(::before wash, ::after corner, slot, layer-center-glow, layer-core-dot)) → ::before ambient → ::after bottom-glow.
  - `is-pure-layout` mode strips containing/animation/pointer-events (sdui.css L26-54).
  - `breaking-news-flash` (core-dot) exposed as imperative method `flash()` via defineExpose.

done:
  - GlassPlayground.vue renders 7 cards (one per status) — pulse/wash/glow visible.
  - Toggling `pureLayout` collapses card to display:contents (verified in DevTools).
  - `flash()` triggers 1s breaking-news-flash and self-resolves.
  - No console warnings; passes Vue strict template typecheck.
